  "local_port": 55426,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some of the best Soft Rock songs of all time?",
  "response": "Soft rock has been a beloved genre for decades, blending the melodic and harmonious elements of rock with softer, more relaxed sounds. Over the years, numerous songs have stood out as classics in this genre. Here's a list of some of the best soft rock songs of all time, spanning different eras and showcasing the versatility of soft rock:\n\n1. **\"Hotel California\" \u2013 Eagles (1977)**\n   - A quintessential soft rock anthem, known for its intricate guitar work and evocative lyrics depicting the excesses of California life.\n\n2. **\"Dreams\" \u2013 Fleetwood Mac (1977)**\n   - A smooth, melodic track featuring Stevie Nicks' haunting vocals, capturing the essence of longing and reflection.\n\n3. **\"Sailing\" \u2013 Christopher Cross (1980)**\n   - This mellow tune won multiple Grammy Awards, celebrated for its soothing melody and calming lyrics about escapism.\n\n4. **\"Your Song\" \u2013 Elton John (1970)**\n   - A heartfelt ballad that showcases Elton John's piano prowess and genuine lyrical expression of love.\n\n5. **\"More Than a Feeling\" \u2013 Boston (1976)**\n   - Combines powerful guitar riffs with melodic hooks, making it a staple in both classic and soft rock playlists.\n\n6. **\"Every Breath You Take\" \u2013 The Police (1983)**\n   - Often mistaken for a love song, its mellow rhythm and haunting lyrics explore themes of obsession and surveillance.\n\n7. **\"Landslide\" \u2013 Fleetwood Mac (1975)**\n   - A beautifully introspective song that highlights Stevie Nicks' delicate vocals and poignant songwriting.\n\n8. **\"Take It Easy\" \u2013 Eagles (1972)**\n   - An upbeat yet relaxed track that embodies the carefree spirit of the early '70s California rock scene.\n\n9. **\"Imagine\" \u2013 John Lennon (1971)**\n   - A timeless soft rock ballad envisioning a world of peace and unity, resonating across generations.\n\n10. **\"Africa\" \u2013 Toto (1982)**\n    - Known for its catchy melody and rich harmonies, this song blends soft rock with African musical influences.\n\n11. **\"Dust in the Wind\" \u2013 Kansas (1977)**\n    - A minimalist acoustic-driven song that contemplates the transient nature of life, paired with soft rock instrumentation.\n\n12. **\"Venus\" \u2013 Bananarama (1986)**\n    - Although leaning towards pop, its soft rock elements and melodic structure have made it a lasting favorite.\n\n13. **\"I Don't Want to Miss a Thing\" \u2013 Aerosmith (1998)**\n    - A power ballad that achieved massive popularity, especially after being featured in the film *Armageddon*.\n\n14. **\"Wonderful Tonight\" \u2013 Eric Clapton (1977)**\n    - A tender love song with a gentle melody, showcasing Clapton's smooth guitar work and heartfelt lyrics.\n\n15. **\"Time After Time\" \u2013 Cyndi Lauper (1983)**\n    - Blends soft rock with pop sensibilities, offering a comforting message of steadfast support and love.\n\n16. **\"Wild World\" \u2013 Cat Stevens (1970)**\n    - A soft rock classic that combines acoustic elements with soulful lyrics about love and change.\n\n17. **\"Rosanna\" \u2013 Toto (1982)**\n    - Features intricate arrangements and a blend of soft rock with pop elements, making it a chart-topping hit.\n\n18. **\"Babe\" \u2013 Styx (1979)**\n    - A soft rock ballad with emotive vocals and a memorable melody, exploring themes of love and loss.\n\n19. **\"Horse with No Name\" \u2013 America (1972)**\n    - Known for its distinctive acoustic sound and mellow vibe, it's a staple in the soft rock genre.\n\n20. **\"Angie\" \u2013 The Rolling Stones (1973)**\n    - A poignant ballad with a softer edge, highlighting the band's versatility beyond their rock roots.\n\nThese songs represent just a fraction of the rich tapestry that is soft rock. They each offer something unique, whether it's poignant lyrics, memorable melodies, or exceptional instrumentation. Exploring these tracks provides a great foundation for understanding and appreciating the depth and appeal of soft rock music.",
